      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): correct model-hallucinated document extensions in file tool path params",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nWhen models blend \"codex\" into office-document extensions (e.g. GPT-5.4 via Codex runtime), they produce hallucinated paths like `report.docodex` instead of `report.docx`. The existing agent-tool path normalization pipeline only strips malformed XML `</arg_value>>` suffixes — it has no awareness of hallucinated file extensions, so these pass through unchanged and cause file-not-found errors.\n\nFixes #93326\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd `correctHallucinatedFileExtension` to the shared agent-tool path normalization pipeline. Known hallucinated extensions (`.docodex`, `.pptcodex`, `.xlscodex`, etc.) are silently corrected to their real counterparts (`.docx`, `.pptx`, `.xlsx`) before filesystem execution.\n\nThe correction reuses the existing `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys` pipeline — no new guard layer, no rejection/retry logic, no behavioral change beyond the extension substitution. Both corrections (XML suffix stripping + hallucinated extension correction) run in sequence within the same normalization pass.\n\n**What changed:**\n- `src/agents/agent-tools.params.ts` — added `HALLUCINATED_EXTENSION_MAP` constant and `correctHallucinatedFileExtension` function; integrated into `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys`\n- `src/agents/agent-tools.read.ts` — added `correctHallucinatedFileExtension` to the direct `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffix` call in `wrapToolWorkspaceRootGuardWithOptions`\n\n**What did NOT change (scope boundary):**\n- No change to agent-tools.read.ts call sites that already use `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys` (the correction is integrated there)\n- No change to bash-tools.exec.ts (already uses `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys`)\n- No new guard layer, no rejection/retry, no new files\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Model-supplied paths like `report.docodex` pass through the current path-normalization pipeline unchanged, causing file-operation failures.\n\n**Environment tested**:\n- Runtime: Node 24.13.1, Linux\n- Code analysis path: `src/agents/agent-tools.params.ts` → `correctHallucinatedFileExtension` / `stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys`\n\n**Steps run after the patch**:\n```bash\nnode --import tsx --no-warnings proof-93326-before-after.mjs\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n\nBEFORE (main branch — bug confirmed):\n```\n=== BEFORE: main branch behavior ===\n  ❌ BUG CONFIRMED: .docodex passes through → {\"path\":\"report.docodex\"}\n  ❌ BUG CONFIRMED: .pptcodex passes through → {\"path\":\"slides.pptcodex\"}\n  ❌ BUG CONFIRMED: .xlscodex passes through → {\"path\":\"budget.xlscodex\"}\n```\n\nAFTER (fix branch — all corrected):\n```\n=== correctHallucinatedFileExtension (standalone) ===\nHallucinated extensions that SHOULD be corrected:\n  PASS: report.docodex → report.docx\n  PASS: path/to/report.docodex → path/to/report.docx\n  PASS: /abs/path/report.docodex → /abs/path/report.docx\n  PASS: slides.pptcodex → slides.pptx\n  PASS: budget.xlscodex → budget.xlsx\n  PASS: report.docxcodex → report.docx\n\nReal extensions that must NOT be modified:\n  PASS: report.docx → report.docx\n  PASS: slides.pptx → slides.pptx\n  PASS: budget.xlsx → budget.xlsx\n  PASS: notes.txt → notes.txt\n\n=== stripMalformedXmlArgValueSuffixFromKeys (pipeline integration) ===\n  PASS: docodex corrected → {\"path\":\"report.docx\"}\n  PASS: real docx unchanged → {\"path\":\"report.docx\"}\n  PASS: XML suffix + docodex both corrected → {\"path\":\"report.docx\"}\n  PASS: pptcodex corrected → {\"path\":\"slides.pptx\"}\n  PASS: xlscodex corrected → {\"path\":\"budget.xlsx\"}\n  PASS: only path corrected, content unchanged → {\"path\":\"report.docx\",\"content\":\"hello\"}\n\n✅ ALL PROOFS PASSED\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Hallucinated extensions are silently corrected in the same normalization pipeline that already strips XML suffixes. Real extensions pass through unchanged.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Gateway/agent session with GPT-5.4 producing hallucinated extensions (no Codex runtime environment available). The correction was verified against the production path-normalization functions directly.",
        "branch": "fix/93326-docx-hallucinated-extension",
